01/10/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis organised a meeting of ministry officials Thursday (30 September) to discuss the expected election of Greece as one of the UN's non-permanent Security Council members for 2005-2006.
The participants reviewed the main institutional, procedural and political issues with which the Security Council is expected to deal, as well as possible Greek initiatives.
The election in New York is scheduled for 15 October.
(ANA - 30/09/04)
